---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../../../components/Header.astro";
import imageLoopTopology from "../images/loop-topology.png";
const { useLayout } = Astro.props;
---

<Layout
 title="Week 2"
 dir="w03/"
 displayLayout={useLayout}
 chapterSubSections={[]}
>
 <Header id="B">
  <h1>Implementing the Plan</h1>
 </Header><div>
  <p class="firstLine">
   How do you put your plan into action? What <strong>tactics</strong> do you use
   to <strong>implement</strong> your strategy? Start by looking at the loop <mark
    >topology</mark
   >.
  </p>
  <img
   src={imageLoopTopology}
   class="right w-1/3 md:w-1/4"
   alt="An illustration showing the loop topology."
  />
  <p>Examine this <strong>guarded</strong> loop. You can see that there are</p>
  <ul>
   <li>actions that occur <mark>before</mark> the loop is encountered</li>
   <li>
    a <strong>test</strong> that determines whether the <mark
     >loop is entered</mark
    >
   </li>
   <li>actions that occur <mark>inside</mark> the loop body</li>
   <li>actions that occur <mark>after</mark> the loop is complete</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
   These four "faces" of a loop are called the <mark>precondition</mark>, the <mark
    >bound</mark
   >, the <mark>action</mark> or
   <mark>operation</mark> and the <mark>postcondition</mark>.
  </p>
  <p>
   Remember these terms; we'll use them to determine exactly <strong
    >where</strong
   > to start working on our loop.
  </p>
 </div>
</Layout>
